J3 = -2.52e-6

In [7]:
# This defines the two-body equation of motions as a system of two vector 
# equations, thus 2x3 = 6 components. 
def deriv(u, dt):
    n = -mu / (u[0] ** 2 + u[1] ** 2 + u[2] ** 2) ** 1.5

    # 
    r_mag = np.sqrt(u[0]**2 + u[1]**2 + u[2]**2)

    #j2 Perturbation
    C1 = ((3/2) * (J2 * mu * re**2)) / r_mag**5
    a_j2_x =C1 * ((5 * u[2]**2)/r_mag**2 - 1)*u[0]
    a_j2_y =C1 * ((5 * u[2]**2)/r_mag**2 - 1)*u[1]
    a_j2_z =C1 * ((5 * u[2]**2)/r_mag**2 -3)*u[2]


    #j3 Perturbation
    C2 = (1/2) * (J3) * (mu / r_mag**2) * (re / r_mag)**3
    zr = u[2] / r_mag

    if calculate_j3 == False:
        a_j3_x = 0
        a_j3_y = 0
        a_j3_z = 0

    if calculate_j3 == True:
        a_j3_x = C2* ( 5 * (7 * zr**3 - 3*zr) * (u[0] / r_mag))
        a_j3_y = C2 * (5 * (7 * zr**3 - 3*zr) * (u[1] / r_mag))
        a_j3_z = C2 * (3 * (   (1) - (10 * zr**2) + ((35 / 3) * zr**4)  ))


    # Ratio, j2 to j3
    #print((a_j3_x/a_j2_x)*100)
    #print((a_j3_y/a_j2_y)*100)
    #print((a_j3_z/a_j2_z)*100)
    #print('----------------')
    return [u[3],     #  dotu[0] = u[3]'
            u[4],     #  dotu[1] = u[4]'
            u[5],     #  dotu[2] = u[5]'
            u[0] * n + a_j2_x + a_j3_x,       #  dotu[3] = u[0] * n
            u[1] * n + a_j2_y + a_j3_y,       #  dotu[4] = u[1] * n
            u[2] * n + a_j2_z + a_j3_z]       #  dotu[5] = u[2] * n
In [8]:
def twobody(nDays):
    #nDays=2 # number of days in simulation
    ElapsedTime = nDays*24*3600  # time of flight in sec
    dt = np.arange(0.0, ElapsedTime, 1)  # define time vector
    #u = odeint(deriv, u0, dt)  # integrate the equations of motion
    u = odeint(deriv, u0, dt, atol=1.0E-20)  # integrate the equations of motion

    x, y, z, x2, y2, z2 = u.T
    r = u[:,0:3]
    v = u[:,3:6]
    return r,v,dt
In [17]:
def plot_trajectory_3d(r_j2):
    fig = plt.figure(figsize=(15,15))
    ax = fig.add_subplot(111, projection = '3d', aspect = 'equal')
    ax.set_xlim([-8000,8000])
    ax.set_ylim([-8000,8000])
    ax.set_zlim([-8000,8000])

    ###########################################
    #Add Earth (Bottom Half)
    u1, v1 = np.mgrid[np.pi:2*np.pi:60j, 0:np.pi:60j]
    xe=re*np.cos(u1)*np.sin(v1)
    ze=re*np.sin(u1)*np.sin(v1)
    ye=re*np.cos(v1)
    clip0 = int(xe.size / 10)
    ax.plot_surface(xe, ye, ze, lw=0.1,alpha=0.5,color='deepskyblue',zorder = -10)

    # Add Earth (Top Half) Used to mask the orbit on the far side of earth.
    u1, v1 = np.mgrid[0:np.pi:60j, 0:np.pi:60j]
    xe=re*np.cos(u1)*np.sin(v1)
    ze=re*np.sin(u1)*np.sin(v1)
    ye=re*np.cos(v1)
    clip0 = int(xe.size / 10)
    ax.plot_surface(xe, ye, ze, lw=0.1,alpha=0.5,color='deepskyblue',zorder = 10)

    ###########################################
    #Plot First Full Orbit
    clip1 = 0
    clip2 = 7500
    ax.plot(r_j2[clip1:clip2,0], r_j2[clip1:clip2,1], r_j2[clip1:clip2,2],'magenta',lw=1,zorder = 2.5)

    #Plot the Bulk of the orbits
    clip3 = dt.size - clip2
    ax.plot(r_j2[clip2:clip3,0], r_j2[clip2:clip3,1], r_j2[clip2:clip3,2],'k',lw=0.05,zorder = 2.5)

    #Plot the Last Full Orbit
    ax.plot(r_j2[clip3:,0], r_j2[clip3:,1], r_j2[clip3:,2],'lime',lw=1,zorder = 2.5)

    ###########################################
    #Label
    ax.set_xlabel('x (km)')
    ax.set_ylabel('y (km)')
    ax.set_zlabel('z (km)')

    #Set ticks
    ax.set_xticks([-5000,0,5000])
    ax.set_yticks([-5000,0,5000])
    ax.set_zticks([-5000,0,5000])

    ax.view_init(elev=6,azim=-55)
In [88]:
def calculate_orbital_elements():

    for i in range(dt.size):
        h = np.cross(r[i],v[i])
        N = np.cross([0,0,1],h)
        eccvec = np.cross(v[i], np.cross(r[i],v[i]))/mu - r[i]/np.linalg.norm(r[i])
        eccmag = la.norm(eccvec)

        energy=v_mag[i]**2 / 2 - mu/r_mag[i]
        a = -mu/(2*energy)
        p = a*(1-eccmag**2)
        I = np.arccos(h[2]/la.norm(h))

        lon_asc_node = np.arccos(N[0]/la.norm(N))

        argp = np.arccos(np.dot(N,eccvec) / (la.norm(N) * la.norm(eccvec)))

        I2[i] = I
        LASCN[i] = lon_asc_node
        ARGP[i] = argp
        A2[i] = a
        H2[i] = la.norm(h)
        E[i] = eccmag
    return I2,LASCN,ARGP,A2,H2,E

In [111]:
def plot_parameter(param,ylab,titl):
    #Linear Regression

    plt.plot(dt,param,c=c_j2,lw=1)

    slope, intercept, r_value, p_value, std_err = stats.linregress(dt,param)
    line = slope*dt+intercept
    plt.plot(dt,line,'r--',lw=1)

    plt.ylabel(ylab+', Semi Major Axis (km)')
    plt.xlabel('time (days)')
    plt.title(titl+', Semi Major Axis, slope={0:0.4e}, b={1:0.4e}'.format(slope,intercept))
